I knew my mother-in-law (Ruth) was a peppermint fan. But I loved spearmint. Every time I would mention spearmint to Ruth she showed no interest. So I decided to take matters into my own hands. My husband David and I went behind closed doors and started experimenting. We wanted a smooth flavorful premium tea to partner with a subtle spearmint flavor. We tried tea after tea to find the perfect combination. Then we set out to find a spearmint grown in America. We tried several spearmints and fell in love with one from a farm out west. column4: my grandmother Ruth Bigelow made the holidays a very special time at Bigelow Tea. She would personally select and then wrap the perfect gift for each and every employee. Ruth would hand deliver the gifts and extend her gratitude to all for their hard work and dedication to her little tea company. This tradition would continue on as our company grew with my parents selecting different gifts for me and my sister Lori to hand out to each employee. Our mother would dress us in matching outfits that she had hand sewn. I was so excited to be a part of this ritual. With each delivery I insisted on hugging and kissing every employee! As the company continues to grow we have found new ways to honor this tradition. Gifts are still given out

Today the Keiller name carries forth the tradition of using only the finest ingredients in their range of premium marmalades and preserves.
